		<title>
		Comment on What’s New in TextExpander: 7.0 Brings New and Improved Features, Accessibility, and a New Learning Center! by Kipp Chambers		</title>
		<link>https://textexpander.com/blog/introducing-te-7#comment-32968</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kipp Chambers]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 05 Nov 2021 16:55:12 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://textexpander.com/?p=28974#comment-32968</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://textexpander.com/blog/introducing-te-7#comment-32678&quot;&gt;John Holter&lt;/a&gt;.

Hi, John - 

Very sorry you&#039;re having trouble updating! The first thing to try is to manually trigger a TextExpander update. To do so, go to TextExpander → Check for Updates. If that works, great!

Based on your message, however, I suspect you&#039;ve already tried that with no luck. If that&#039;s the case, your best bet may be to manually reinstall TextExpander. To do so, please delete TextExpander from your Windows or Mac machine (don&#039;t worry - your snippets are tied to your account and won&#039;t be lost). Then just visit this page:

https://textexpander.com/download

...download the latest version and install it. You should then be able to open TextExpander, sign in, and get back to expanding.

If the above doesn&#039;t work, please reach out to our support team via the following link - they should be able to help you resolve the issue.

https://textexpander.com/contact

Very sorry again for the trouble!]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://textexpander.com/blog/introducing-te-7#comment-32678">John Holter</a>.</p>
<p>Hi, John &#8211; </p>
<p>Very sorry you&#8217;re having trouble updating! The first thing to try is to manually trigger a TextExpander update. To do so, go to TextExpander → Check for Updates. If that works, great!</p>
<p>Based on your message, however, I suspect you&#8217;ve already tried that with no luck. If that&#8217;s the case, your best bet may be to manually reinstall TextExpander. To do so, please delete TextExpander from your Windows or Mac machine (don&#8217;t worry &#8211; your snippets are tied to your account and won&#8217;t be lost). Then just visit this page:</p>
<p><a href="https://textexpander.com/download" rel="nofollow ugc">https://textexpander.com/download</a></p>
<p>&#8230;download the latest version and install it. You should then be able to open TextExpander, sign in, and get back to expanding.</p>
<p>If the above doesn&#8217;t work, please reach out to our support team via the following link &#8211; they should be able to help you resolve the issue.</p>
<p><a href="https://textexpander.com/contact" rel="nofollow ugc">https://textexpander.com/contact</a></p>
<p>Very sorry again for the trouble!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
			</item>
